@halcy you were right, python does easily handle the unnamed constructors and the tests were only failing because of the reordering of the constructor parameters I had done.
Tests should be fine now and the only different is that an error will be raised if no parameters are passed at all.

Also sorry about the several pull requests. Still learning how to clean these up.

