a mockup for property-like event handler decorators

```python
class A(HasTraits):
    i = Int()

    # kwargs can be passed
    @i.observer(type='change')
    def i(self, change):
        print('i changed')

    # the generalized api
    @i.decorate(ValidateHandler)
    def i(self, commit):
        return commit['value']*2

    # streamlined api
    @i.default
    def i(self):
        return 1
    
class B(A):
    
    @A.i.default
    def i(self):
        return 2
```

The reason this isn't particularly clean to implement under the hood is because the decorator is run prior to when the trait has received its `name` attribute.

